ta\";s:31:\"Thu, 06 Apr 2017 18:14:43 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Using MailChimp\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"education\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"resources\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"udacity\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"https://blog.mailchimp.com/?p=103989\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:346:\"When we talk to customers who run small businesses, many of them say that marketing is the hardest part. It’s possible to be a charismatic leader with great ideas, a creative genius, or a wizard of sales and still feel a little lost when it comes to SEO, social media ads, and email marketing.\r\n\r\nThat’s where our friends at Udacity come in. \";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"Katie\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1601:\"<figure class=\"img full-width\"><img src=\"https://blog.mailchimp.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/udacity_nanodegree_1344-1008x605.jpg\" /></figure>\n<p>When we talk to customers who run small businesses, many of them say that marketing is the hardest part. It’s possible to be a charismatic leader with great ideas, a creative genius, or a wizard of sales and still feel a little lost when it comes to <a href=\"https://blog.mailchimp.com/what-is-seo/\" target=\"_blank\">SEO</a>, <a href=\"https://blog.mailchimp.com/making-the-best-facebook-ads-in-mailchimp/\" target=\"_blank\">Facebook ads</a>, and email marketing.</p>\n<p>Sometimes, it’s because of time constraints. People running a small business are often doing the jobs of 3 or 4 people, and maintaining the proper amount of inventory is enough of a struggle without adding advanced segmentation to the to-do list.</p>\n<p>But often, it’s simply a matter of knowing where to start. That’s where our friends at Udacity come in. They’ve developed an online program designed to give you a comprehensive education in digital marketing in just 3 months. MailChimp and other top companies collaborated on lessons to help you master our platforms and the fundamentals of our marketing specialties.</p>\n<p>If you’re looking to learn and want hands-on experience and mentoring, but can’t devote yourself to it full-time, <a href=\"https://www.udacity.com/digital-marketing?utm_source=Mailchimp&amp;utm_medium=Content&amp;utm_campaign=DMNDlaunch\" target=\"_blank\">Udacity’s digital marketing nanodegree program</a> is worth a look.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:29:\"http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/\";a:1:{s:7:\"content\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:2:{s:3:\"url\";s:89:\"https://blog.mailchimp.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/udacity_nanodegree_1344-600x360.jpg\";s:6:\"medium\";s:5:\"image\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5: